<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: OJAI; 
</P>
<P>
CITY DELAYS BAN ON WATER-WELL DRILLING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THIA BELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Ojai City Council this week delayed adoption of an emergency ban on 
drilling water wells. 
</P>
<P>
Consideration of the measure was delayed until Oct. 9 after City Atty. 
</P>
<P>
Monte Widders asked for more time to research legal issues involved in banning 
well drilling where a water shortage exists. 
</P>
<P>
The Casitas Municipal Water District declared an emergency shortage throughout 
the Ojai Valley in April that could continue indefinitely. Southern California 
Water Co., which has held the city's water franchise since 1948 and has 
proposed drilling a new well just outside the city limits, submitted a letter 
to the city objecting to the proposed six-month ban. 
</P>
<P>
Although the company's plan would not be affected by a city ban, the letter 
says well drilling is a matter of private property rights. THIA BELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
