task force examining the deaths of 43 women, mostly prostitutes and transients, 
was a subject of a 1985 internal affairs investigation into allegations that he 
and other officers had sex with prostitute Cynthia Maine, at left. Maine, who 
worked as a police informant, disappeared in 1986. BOB GRIESER / Los Angeles 
