<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPOTLIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Occidental Coach Bill Harvey is wary of crediting one athlete for the success 
of this year's team, but it is difficult not to notice the Tigers' No. 1 
runner. 
</P>
<P>
Beltran, a junior transfer from Fullerton Junior College, led Occidental to a 
seventh-place finish in the Fresno Invitational on Sept. 15 and helped the 
Tigers to a convincing double-dual meet victory over Redlands and Pomona-Pitzer 
last Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
He finished ninth in Fresno against a field of predominantly Division I runners 
and smashed the five-mile course record at Redlands with a time of 26 minutes 
59.7 seconds. 
</P>
<P>
"He's certainly a very good runner and very experienced," Harvey said of 
Beltran, a native of Mexico and the national junior college record-holder in 
the marathon (2:17:26). "But there's a lot more to his life than running. He's 
a very fine student and a highly motivated one. 
</P>
<P>
"School's going to come first with him no matter how he runs." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Marcial Beltran: Occidental Cross-country Junior 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
