<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SIERRA MADRE; 
</P>
<P>
TERM LIMITS FOR VOLUNTEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Members of City Council-appointed committees, commissions and boards may not 
serve more than two consecutive terms in their volunteer positions, according 
to a new ordinance adopted by the City Council Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The six advisory bodies affected are the planning, parks and recreation, 
emergency services and cultural heritage commissions; library board of 
trustees, and waste management task force/recycling committee. 
</P>
<P>
Members previously could serve an unlimited number of terms of two to four 
years, depending on the body. 
</P>
<P>
The new limit applies to members after the expiration of their current terms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
