<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
PHOTO GALLERY GETS GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Santa Monica College Photography Gallery, the only public gallery in the 
Los Angeles area devoted exclusively to the photographic arts, has received a 
$2,323 grant from the California Arts Council. 
</P>
<P>
The money will be used to help operate the gallery and expand efforts to reach 
out to minority and other communities to increase attendance and participation 
in gallery programs, said Robert Godwin, gallery director. 
</P>
<P>
The gallery, which opened in 1988 and is located in the college's library 
foyer, has exhibited a wide range of works of renowned artists from around the 
world. 
</P>
