<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
PERMIT PARKING ZONE OKD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council Tuesday night introduced an ordinance establishing a 
preferential parking zone in the area surrounding the Santa Monica Hospital and 
Medical Center. 
</P>
<P>
Non-residential parking will be restricted to two hours between 9 a.m. and 9 
p.m. on weekdays and from 3 p.m. to 9 p.m. on weekends. 
</P>
<P>
The parking zone is bounded by 14th Street, Wilshire Boulevard, 20th Street and 
Santa Monica Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
The ordinance is a compromise between residents, who wanted no parking for 
non-residents, and the nearby churches and businesses that did not want any 
restrictions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
