<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
BUSINESS LICENSE REVISIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Business license tax revisions Tuesday by the Board of Directors will bring the 
city $530,980 annually in new revenue. 
</P>
<P>
Property owners renting commercial or industrial space to others will pay fees 
of $100 on the first 1,000 square feet of space rented and $10 for each 
additional 1,000 square feet. Those occupying space in their own buildings will 
receive a 50% fee reduction. 
</P>
<P>
In addition, the delinquent business license fee will increase and those who do 
not obtain business licenses will be fined. 
</P>
</TEXT>
