<HEADLINE>
<P>
2 LOADED FREIGHT TRAILERS STOLEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two freight trailers, one loaded with Christmas mugs and plastic tumblers, were 
stolen from a freight company's parking lot across from the Northeast Division 
police station on San Fernando Road in Glassell Park, Los Angeles police said 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
Employees noticed the trailers missing from the lot in the 3400 block of San 
Fernando Road Tuesday morning and notified police, said Officer Enrique 
Conrado. 
</P>
<P>
Police believe a tractor rig was used to haul the trailers off the lot sometime 
between Friday afternoon and Tuesday morning. 
</P>
<P>
Other empty and more accessible trailers were ignored, police said. The 
trailers had arrived at the facility Friday from docks in San Pedro. 
</P>
<P>
One of the trailers contained about $33,000 worth of mugs and plastic tumblers 
and the other contained about $46,000 worth of an unknown type of gift sets. 
</P>
</TEXT>
