NAMES IN THE NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Western Washington University running back Mike Wagner, the former St. Monica 
High School star, scored four touchdowns last week in a 30-22 victory over 
Western Oregon State. 
</P>
<P>
The four touchdowns set a single-game record for Western Washington, an NAIA 
school in Bellingham. 
</P>
<P>
He also established a Columbia Football Assn. record for most touchdowns 
rushing in one game. 
</P>
<P>
In his team's only other game this season, a 22-19 loss to Whitworth College, 
Wagner, The Times' 1988 Westside Back of the Year, scored two touchdowns. His 
average of 18 points a game puts him in a four-way tie for first in the nation 
among NAIA players. 
</P>
<P>
Gail Weldon, owner of a Westside fitness facility and director of physical 
therapy and trainer at the 1984 Olympic Games, has been named director of 
medical services for the U.S. Olympic Festival -- '91, in Los Angeles next 
July. 
</P>
