<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: DEPUTIES SEIZE 8 GALLONS OF PCP, ARREST 
SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
One man was arrested and sheriff's deputies seized about 8 gallons of the 
potent hallucinogenic drug PCP worth about $85,000 in a raid on a Willowbrook 
home, authorities said Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Deputy John Ashley said a gang enforcement team on routine patrol smelled the 
drug's characteristic strong odor along the 2000 block of East 130th Street 
about 11:45 p.m. Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The deputies noticed one suspect carrying two one-quart beer bottles and a 
second suspect fled on foot as the officers got out of their patrol car. The 
bottles smelled of PCP, Ashley said. 
</P>
<P>
Deputies searched the house and found the drug in two 5-gallon gasoline cans. 
The house apparently was not being lived in, he said. 
</P>
<P>
Robbie Anderson, 24, of Lynwood, was arrested on suspicion of manufacturing and 
possession of PCP. He was held in lieu of $100,000 bail. The second suspect was 
being sought, Ashley said. 
</P>
