<HEADLINE>
<P>
SURGERY IS SET MONDAY FOR BLYLEVEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Angel right-hander Bert Blyleven will undergo arthroscopic surgery on his right 
shoulder Monday in an effort to repair a problem that has reduced strength in 
the shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
A club spokesman said Blyleven might have a slight tear in the rotator cuff, 
and the arthroscopic procedure was scheduled because Blyleven hasn't responded 
as well as expected to treatment and therapy. 
</P>
<P>
Team physician Lewis Yocum will perform the procedure. 
</P>
<P>
Blyleven, 39, hasn't pitched since Aug. 10. He is 8-7 with a 5.24 earned-run 
average this season and has 279 victories. He was signed to a guaranteed 
contract for 1991 at slightly more than $2 million. HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</TEXT>
