<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT / WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
USC; 
</P>
<P>
HISTORY FAVORS TROJANS AT OHIO STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Good news for USC fans: 
</P>
<P>
 -- The last time USC was shut out before last week, a 24-0 loss to Arizona 
State in 1985, the Trojans came back the next week to rout Oregon State, 63-0. 
The 87-point turnaround was the biggest in Trojan history. 
</P>
<P>
 -- Larry Smith is 3-0 against Ohio State Coach John Cooper. 
</P>
<P>
Before Smith and USC beat Cooper and Ohio State last season, 42-3, Smith and 
Arizona twice beat Cooper and Arizona State. The Wildcats knocked Arizona State 
out of a Rose Bowl bid with a 16-13 victory in 1985 and won again the next 
year, 34-17, handing the Sun Devils their only loss of a 10-1-1 season that 
included a 22-15 victory over Michigan in the Rose Bowl. JERRY CROWE 
</P>
</TEXT>
