<P>
GRETZKY LEADS KINGS PAST CANUCKS, 5-3 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SEATTLE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wayne Gretzky scored twice and added two assists Wednesday night to lead the 
Kings to a 5-3 victory over the Vancouver Canucks in a National Hockey League 
exhibition game. 
</P>
<P>
The Kings scored two third-period goals to break a 3-3 tie. 
</P>
<P>
Just over two minutes into the final period, Todd Elik scored off an assist 
from Francois Breault. 
</P>
<P>
Gretzky added the clincher at 5:35 with his second goal of the game coming on a 
power play. 
</P>
<P>
The Kings improved to 5-3. Vancouver dropped to 1-4-2. 
</P>
<P>
Each team has two remaining exhibitions before opening the regular season Oct. 
4. 
</P>
<P>
The attendance was 9,936, nearly 5,000 short of capacity in the Seattle 
Coliseum. The NHL will expand by two teams for the 1992-93 season and Seattle 
is one of eight cities in the running for an expansion team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
