<HEADLINE>
<P>
VOLUNTEERS SOUGHT FOR 4-HOUR HOSPITAL SHIFTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONG BEACH 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dominguez Medical Center is seeking volunteers to work in guest relations, 
reception, nursing and clerical units. 
</P>
<P>
Individuals must be 16 or older. Persons with bilingual skills are encouraged 
to apply. Volunteers should be willing to commit a minimum of four hours per 
week. They will be provided with a uniform and receive a free meal after every 
four-hour shift. 
</P>
<P>
For more information, call the Volunteer Services Program at 609-3822. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA092790-0157 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 284004 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
September 27, 1990, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Long Beach; Part J; Page 6; Column 2 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
