<HEADLINE>
<P>
GRAND PRIX BIKE RACES SET OCT. 14 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WHITTIER 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Some of the country's top professional bicycle racers will compete in the first 
Whittier Grand Prix at noon Oct. 14 on a 45-mile course along the streets of 
the city's uptown section. 
</P>
<P>
Among the 80 racers who will try to win a share of the $10,000 purse will be 
Kurt Stockton of Santa Barbara, the U.S. men's open champion. 
</P>
<P>
There will be seven other races in various categories, including four open to 
community residents. The first race will start at 7:30 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
The races will benefit the Boys and Girls clubs of Whittier. There will also be 
a health and fitness fair. For more information, call 803-1993. 
</P>
