<P>
Food; Part H; Page 40; Column 5 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
100 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRIENDS OF THE RAT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SARI REZNICK, San Diego 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Food section's Newsbites column (Sept. 6) contained a short article about 
rats who died of respiratory failure after ingesting large quantities of hot 
sauce. 
</P>
<P>
The article was light in tone and admonished readers not to drink quarts of hot 
sauce or "shoot up" with hot sauce lest they suffer a similar fate. Can you 
imagine, however, the suffering involved in this reported experiment? Obviously 
the rats didn't rush to overindulge a hot-sauce passion -- they must have been 
force-fed. A death by respiratory failure, for man, rat, dog, horse, etc. is a 
horrible one. SARI REZNICK, San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
