MAN FOUND SHOT DEAD AT PLACE OF BUSINESS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
ANAHEIM 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Cypress man was found shot to death at his business Wednesday morning by 
employees arriving for work, police said. 
</P>
<P>
The body of Jess Michael Jewett, 36, was discovered in an upstairs room at the 
business, A-J Sheet Metal Inc., 1845 S. Lewis St., about 8:20 a.m., Police Lt. 
Marc Hedgpeth said. Hedgpeth said Jewett received "several gunshots to the 
upper body," but he would not elaborate. 
</P>
