<P>
Injection Wells Ordered Closed: Six Southern California firms were told by the 
Environmental Protection Agency to halt underground dumping of contaminated 
fluids. Part of an ongoing EPA enforcement effort, the firms were accused of 
violating the federal Safe Drinking Water Act -- but not posing an immediate 
danger to any drinking water supplies -- by disposing of oil, degreasing 
solvents and other wastes in the wells. Named were: Ball &amp; Sons Auto, 
Malibu; Sierra Toyota, Lancaster; Trancas Canyon Chevron, Malibu; Foothill 
Chevrolet, La Canada; B. &amp; H. Repair, Corona, and Daily Tire &amp; 
Automotive, Newhall. 
