Senators Urge Aid for Pickens: Thirty two senators urged the Bush 
Administration to pressure Koito Manufacturing Co., a Japanese auto parts 
supplier, into seating corporate raider T. Boone Pickens Jr. on its board. 
Although Pickens is Koito's largest single shareholder, the firm's management 
