<P>
CHAMBER'S NEW VIDEO LIBRARY FOR OWNERS MAKES ITS DEBUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Cristina Lee / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Greater Santa Ana Chamber of Commerce on Wednesday opened Orange County's 
first video library for small businesses. 
</P>
<P>
The Business Media Center contains a series of 30-minute videos, developed by 
the chamber and Pacific Bell, that provide small business owners tips on 
financing, marketing and management. 
</P>
<P>
The initial videos are in English but videos dubbed in Spanish, Vietnamese and 
Cambodian will be available soon, said Michael Metzler, the chamber's 
president. 
</P>
<P>
The library is the brainchild of insurance agent Paul Park, a chamber member, 
and is open to members only. 
</P>
<P>
"This is a prototype model for other chambers of commerce in the nation to 
follow," Park said. "This will provide business owners the necessary 
information to run their companies efficiently by using local businessmen to 
discuss local business problems." 
</P>
<P>
Comcast Cable TV (Channels 3 and 26) in Santa Ana agreed to air some of the 
videos in October, Metzler said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
